 and the Champs-Elysees in the heart of Paris ahead of what is sure to be 11 days of intense competition.\", \"from\": 775, \"to\": 1091, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 779, \"end\": 785, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.660617902972408, \"rank\": 0.5086558937868473, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 966, \"end\": 986, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6960305261495696e-17, \"text\": \"Place de la Concorde\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\"}, {\"begin\": 995, \"end\": 1009, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"score\": 0.9992163039517089, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Champs-Elysees\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\"}, {\"begin\": 1026, \"end\": 1031, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.152202949519747e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremony's artistic director Thomas Jolly has revealed the spectacle will \\\"showcase the Paralympic athletes and the values that they embody\\\".\", \"from\": 1093, \"to\": 1246, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1134, \"end\": 1140, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"score\": 0.9625663036637064, \"rank\": 0.03888627332200699, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has promised \\\"performances that have never been seen before\\\" and claims that the show will \\\"unite spectators and television audiences worldwide around the unique spirit of the Paralympic Games\\\".\", \"from\": 1247, \"to\": 1444, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow all the latest updates from the Paralympics opening ceremony with our live blog below:  Just days beforeParalympianslast gathered for their Winter Games in Beijing, Russian tanks rolled across the border into Ukraine.\", \"from\": 1446, \"to\": 1670, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1609, \"end\": 1616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999989346414529, \"rank\": 1.0653699100044483e-05, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1618, \"end\": 1625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"score\": 0.9650815512449872, \"rank\": 0.030766985972396438, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1662, \"end\": 1669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9982580630264483, \"rank\": 0.0017449753939961052, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One year later Yevhenii Korinets, from Zhytomyr Oblast on the border of Belarus, lost his leg during a bitter fire fight in Minkivka.\", \"from\": 1672, \"to\": 1805, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1711, \"end\": 1726, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhytomyr_Oblast\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zhytomyr Oblast\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhytomyr_Oblast\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhytomyr_Oblast\"}, {\"begin\": 1744, \"end\": 1751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\", \"score\": 0.999992418086643, \"rank\": 7.538807413251659e-06, \"text\": \"Belarus\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Life can come at you faster than a double amputee sprinter on carbon-fibre blades sometimes, with Korinets making his Paralympic debut as a sitting volleyball player this week.\", \"from\": 1807, \"to\": 1983, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Six years ago, Canadian rower Jacob Wassermann was paralysed from the waist down in a bus crash that claimed the lives of 16 of his junior ice hockey team-mates.\", \"from\": 1985, \"to\": 2146, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2000, \"end\": 2008, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9997054076918411, \"rank\": 0.0002946722883059876, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}, {\"begin\": 2021, \"end\": 2031, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wolfgang_Voigt\", \"score\": 0.9381741176400907, \"rank\": 0.06529799719895843, \"text\": \"Wassermann\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wolfgang_Voigt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wolfgang_Voigt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Australian table tennis hope Ma Lin was just five years old when his right arm was eaten by a brown bear during a family trip to a zoo in China.\", \"from\": 2147, \"to\": 2291, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2176, \"end\": 2182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ma_Lin_(table_tennis)\", \"score\": 0.6992745119654403, \"rank\": 0.24012717536812367, \"text\": \"Ma Lin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13382519\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ma_Lin_(table_tennis)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ma_Lin_(table_tennis)\"}, {\"begin\": 2285, \"end\": 2290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999981085938695, \"rank\": 1.6569198385648271e-06, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Two torch bearers receive the Paralympic flame and head over to the cauldron.\", \"from\": 2293, \"to\": 2370, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They sweep up the last ramp hand-in-hand and offload the flame to three more athletes who will perform the final act.\", \"from\": 2371, \"to\": 2488, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a combined honour that all five of them perform together.\", \"from\": 2490, \"to\": 2552, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The cauldron is lit!\", \"from\": 2554, \"to\": 2574, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paralympic Games have begun!\", \"from\": 2575, \"to\": 2607, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Off go the fireworks to signify the end of the routine.\", \"from\": 2609, \"to\": 2664, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The flame begins its final trup towards the cauldron.\", \"from\": 2665, \"to\": 2718, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There is a silence over the arena with just the background music playing as the flame is ran out of the Place do Concorde before heading to its final destination.\", \"from\": 2720, \"to\": 2882, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ravel's Bolero is the soundtrack to this final dance.\", \"from\": 2884, \"to\": 2937, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2884, \"end\": 2889, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maurice_Ravel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ravel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maurice_Ravel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maurice_Ravel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's been a far more classical and traditional ceremony than the Olympics one was.\", \"from\": 2938, \"to\": 3020, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The flame is slowly making it's way across the stage.\", \"from\": 3022, \"to\": 3075, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here it is!\", \"from\": 3077, \"to\": 3088, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The final formal act of the opening ceremony sees all the 150 performing torch bearers stood in the shadow of the obelisk.\", \"from\": 3090, \"to\": 3212, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They begin a final dance to signify the concorde of sport.\", \"from\": 3213, \"to\": 3271, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The flames are about to come together.\", \"from\": 3273, \"to\": 3311, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"French artist S\\u00e9bastien Tellier performs 'La Ritournelle', accompanied by an impressive lightshow designed by Thomas Dechandon.\", \"from\": 3313, \"to\": 3440, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3313, \"end\": 3319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.660617902972408, \"rank\": 0.5086558937868473, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3327, \"end\": 3344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/S\\u00e9bastien_Tellier\", \"score\": 0.9999999785604816, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"S\\u00e9bastien Tellier\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/S\\u00e9bastien_Tellier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/S\\u00e9bastien_Tellier\"}, {\"begin\": 3423, \"end\": 3429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"score\": 0.9625663036637064, \"rank\": 0.03888627332200699, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All this while we wait for the Paralympic flame to arrive.\", \"from\": 3442, \"to\": 3500, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paralympic flames arrive in Paris.\", \"from\": 3502, \"to\": 3540, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3534, \"end\": 3539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.152202949519747e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A video shows the journey they have taken to get here.\", \"from\": 3541, \"to\": 3595, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On its arrival on French soil, the Flame was divided into 12 Flames, to reflect the number of days of the Paralympic Games.\", \"from\": 3597, \"to\": 3720, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3615, \"end\": 3621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.660617902972408, \"rank\": 0.5086558937868473, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"1,000 Torchbearers spread the energy of the Games throughout France, highlighting regions committed to promoting inclusion in sport and raising awareness of disability issues.\", \"from\": 3722, \"to\": 3897, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3783, \"end\": 3789, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999999419371475, \"rank\": 5.687016767171347e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The next formality is the Paralympic Oath.\", \"from\": 3899, \"to\": 3941, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Two Paralympic athletes, a judge and a coach take the Oath on behalf of their peers and pledge to respect and promote the Paralympic values of determination, equality, inspiration and courage.\", \"from\": 3943, \"to\": 4135, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As the flag is raised, the Paralympic anthem is played which is joyous and inspiring.\", \"from\": 4137, \"to\": 4222, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4164, \"end\": 4181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_symbols\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paralympic anthem\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_symbols\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_symbols\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The crowd is hushed as they witness this next stage of the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 4223, \"to\": 4299, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a special moment, one of many we have witnessed this evening.\", \"from\": 4301, \"to\": 4367, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 4369, \"to\": 4599, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4420, \"end\": 4431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.591829274919e-16, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}]}]}"